title: How Nadeshot Built the World of 100 Thieves
video_description:
Before you tell your story, first, you need to make your map.

Creators like us are small companies, and if we craft our own evergreen worlds, we can defy Father Time and make things that last. For Essay 5, we looked at Matthew "Nadeshot" Haag and the steps he took to build the world of 100 Thieves.

Season.1, dubbed 'Transitions,' is all about reflecting on Powder Blue's past while introducing our future building as partner with creators to build their worlds. Sign up at laylo.com/powderblue to get notified of all future content and product drops.

video_description:

Season 1, dubbed 'Transitions,' is all about reflecting on Powder Blue's past while introducing our future as we release the first-ever magazine dedicated to covering the creator economy. Sign up at laylo.com/powderblue to get notified of all future content and product drops.

title: The Rise and Fall of All Gas No Brakes (Teaser)
video_description:
When Andrew Callaghan graduated with a journalism degree in 2019, he decided to hit the road in an RV with his two best friends, to chronicle everything weird and wild about our country.

The show, 'All Gas No Brakes', racked up millions of views. Yet in November 2020, Andrew strangely stopped posting to his YouTube account. And in March, the truth came out: somehow, he lost the show he had built from the ground up.

title: Unboxing Our Official Sandwich
video_description:
We collaborated with D&D Finer Foods on Noyes Street in Evanston to support with a story, podcast, three unique products, and this incredible, limited-edition sandwich.

Featuring classic ham-and-swiss on toasted ciabatta bread, "The Unplug" has all of the essentials: lettuce, tomato, onions...you know the drill. However, it's the mayo and honey mustard combo that really puts this thing over the top; when the owner of the store is even calling the sandwich delicious, that's when you know it's a must-have.

Stop by D&D's to pick up a sandwich through the end of the week and learn more about the collab at unplugwithus.com/dnds!

title: Chess Is A Sport: The Hot Takes Show Ep. 2
video_description:
We're baaaaaccckkkk! 'The Hot Takes Show' returns with host Andrew Fenichel to determine the best hot take artist around. On this episode, Ben Curwin argues why the letter 'c' should be taken out of the alphabet, while Peter Warren makes the case for chess as a sport.

Created by Nathan Graber-Lipperman and Andrew Fenichel, 'The Hot Takes Show' celebrates the thing we all love to hate and hate to love: hot takes. On each episode, two panelists enter; however, only one of them can ultimately secure the bag.

'The Hot Takes Show' is brought to you by Powder Blue Media and was created, shot, and edited at Northwestern University in Evanston, IL. To learn more about Powder Blue, log on at unplugwithus.com and follow us on Twitter @unplugg_d.

title: The Hot Takes Show Ep. 1: A Beanie Is Not A Hat
video_description:
In the pilot episode of "The Hot Takes Show," Jake Liker argues why a beanie isn't a hat, while George Irving shares his thoughts on why umbrellas are dumb. Host Andrew Fenichel moderates the conversation, determines who has the hotter take, and makes sure to stop by downtown Chicago to hear what the people of the city had to say about the beanie debate.

At its core, THTS is a satirical take on Hot Take Culture. Nothing truly productive can come out of an hour-long show where two grown men yell at each other; thatâ€™s just not how discourse is intended to work. Itâ€™s inherently silly and should be treated as such, and thatâ€™s what we intended to channel in creating our show.

For more great content, make sure to check out our website at powderbluemedia.com. Follow us on social media and subscribe to our YouTube channel to keep up with our upcoming projects!
